Description: Fragment of strap handle of a pottery transport amphora. Clay fine cream-buff; light purple core; some mica. Circular stamp.
Curator's comments: Trimmed. The clay points to Corinth or Cocyra, though the strap handle does not.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1726)
